## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="17c91-159">En el ejemplo siguiente se crea una gramática que reconoce la frase "es de un país que ha ganado la Copa del mundo" seguido del nombre de un país que ha ganado la Copa del mundo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="17c91-159">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="17c91-160">Después de crear el <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> objeto `winnerRule` y dándole el identificador de cadena `WorldCupWinner`, el ejemplo se usa el <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A> método para anexar la cadena "es de un país que ha ganado la Copa del mundo" para la regla.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="17c91-160">After creating the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object `winnerRule` and giving it the string identifier `WorldCupWinner`, the example uses the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A> method to append the string  "A nation that has won the World Cup is" to the rule.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="17c91-161">En el ejemplo, a continuación, crea dos reglas adicionales, `ruleEurope` y `ruleSAmerica`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="17c91-161">The example then creates two additional rules, `ruleEurope` and  `ruleSAmerica`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="17c91-162">Nuevo con el <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A> método, el ejemplo agrega un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> de objeto para el `WorldCupWinner` regla que contiene las referencias de regla a `ruleEurope` y `ruleSAmerica`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="17c91-162">Again using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A> method, the example appends an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object to the `WorldCupWinner` rule that contains rule references to `ruleEurope` and `ruleSAmerica`.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
// Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule  
// and set its scope to public.  
SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
// Add the introduction.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
// Create the rule for the European nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"), new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
// Create the rule for the South American nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"), new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
// Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
// Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
// the root rule of the document.  
document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
document.Root = winnerRule;  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="17c91-192">El valor predeterminado para el ámbito es `Private`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="17c91-192">The default value for scope is `Private`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="17c91-193">Una regla privada sólo puede activarse para el reconocimiento mediante una referencia de regla de la regla raíz de su gramática contenedora o de otra regla que se hace referencia desde la regla raíz.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="17c91-193">A private rule can only be activated for recognition by a rule reference from the root rule in its containing grammar or from another rule that is referenced from the root rule.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="17c91-194">Una regla privada no se puede hacer referencia a una gramática externa, a menos que la regla privada se declara como la regla raíz de su gramática contenedora.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="17c91-194">A private rule cannot be referenced by an external grammar, unless the private rule is declared as the root rule of its containing grammar.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="17c91-195">Si se establece su ámbito en `Public`, un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> objeto puede activarse para el reconocimiento mediante una referencia desde un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef> objeto en la gramática contenedora o desde una regla en una gramática externa.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="17c91-195">If its scope is set to `Public`, an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object can be activated for recognition by a reference from a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef> object in the containing grammar or from a rule in an external grammar.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="17c91-196">En el ejemplo siguiente se crea una gramática que reconoce la frase "es de un país que ha ganado la Copa del mundo" seguido del nombre de un país que ha ganado la Copa del mundo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="17c91-196">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="17c91-197">Crea una regla pública denominada `WorldCupWinner` y establece el ámbito de esa regla al público.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="17c91-197">It creates a public rule named `WorldCupWinner` and sets the scope of that rule to Public.</span></span>  
  
